SUMMARY:[FSE Doctoral Symposium] Towards Trustworthy AI-Enabled Systems: From Model-Level Reliability to Systemic Assurance - Yuheng Huang
DESCRIPTION:The rapid integration of opaque AI models into critical software infrastructure creates a fundamental challenge for reliability and trustworthiness. This paper addresses this dilemma through the philosophy of Decoding Complexity by Gaining Insight through Systematic Interaction. We present a body of work organized around two research questions: Testing &amp\; Characterization (RQ1)\, which focuses on automated input generation and boundary probing to reveal hidden behaviors\, and Enhancement &amp\; Assurance (RQ2)\, which leverages mined behavioral patterns to engineer active defenses and runtime monitoring. Having made numerous successful attempts across a broad spectrum of AI models and diverse tasks\, we outline a future agenda to scale this paradigm to the broader AI lifecycle and more complex AI systems.\n
LOCATION:MB 3.210 - 1450 Guy St, Montreal, Quebec H3H 0A1, Montreal, Canada
LAST-MODIFIED:20260616T191344Z
END:VEVENT
